{"id": 7647, "title": "Ticket #7647: UW condor 8.9.7 RPM does not pull in Python bindings", "description": "<blockquote>\n\"yum install condor\" from the UW repos does not bring in python2-condor or python3-condor, even though it is required for classad_eval.\n\n<p>It's not an explicit Requires in the spec file -- I'm guessing we're expecting RPM's automatic dependency generator to pick it up... but then there's this chunk of code:\n\n</p><p></p><pre>  %if %uw_build\n  %define __find_requires %{SOURCE90}\n  %define _use_internal_dependency_generator 0\n  %endif\n</pre>\n\n<p>We should make sure the dependency on the Python bindings is correctly added.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Jul-31 17:39</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=60298\">[60298]</a></span>: Version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7500\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7500'); return false;\" title=\"Clients should not suggest authentication methods they don't support\">#7500</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7627\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7627'); return false;\" title=\"Support CPU affinity with Docker\">#7627</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7647\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7647'); return false;\" title=\"UW condor 8.9.7 RPM does not pull in Python bindings\">#7647</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7712\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7712'); return false;\" title='Add \"--debug\" option to bosco_cluster'>#7712</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7753\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7753'); return false;\" title=\"RHEL-based Bosco tarballs using the wrong version\">#7753</a></span>  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Jun-29 19:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=60029\">[60029]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7647\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7647'); return false;\" title=\"UW condor 8.9.7 RPM does not pull in Python bindings\">#7647</a></span>) Ensure that python3-condor is installed. On EL7, python2-condor is also required because some scripts import requests and python3-requests is not available for EL7.  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2020-Jul-31 17:40", "status": "resolved", "created": "2020-May-20 16:05", "fixed_version": "2020-May-20 16:05", "broken_version": "v080907", "priority": "4", "subsystem": "Packaging", "assigned_to": "tim", "derived_from": "", "creator": "matyas", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "matyas@cs.wisc.edu karpel@wisc.edu", "due_date": ""}